  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n### Description\r\nSender's address is not part of the transaction hash calculation which causes `Transaction already imported error` when sending the same transaction from 2 different accounts in manual mine mode.\r\n\r\nFrom looking at the source code looks like the `from` address is not used when calculating the transaction hash.\r\n\r\nThis causes hash collision when 2 accounts with the same nonce send the same transaction.\r\n\r\n### Example\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37778340/203745678-aa64ea5d-32ea-40b0-9dba-49528f32e11e.png)\r\n\r\n* When running the code above on Anvil (`anvil -f https://eth-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/xxxxx-xxxxxxxxx-xxx_xxxxxx_xx --no-mining --fork-block-number 16038646`) we get the following error: `code\":-32003,\"message\":\"transaction already imported\"}`\r\n* When running the same code on similarly configured Hardhat the execution is succesful.\r\n",
